
[1]sacrilegious

   SACRILE'GIOUS, a. [L. sacrilegus.]

   1. Violating sacred things; polluted with the crime of sacrilege.

   Above the reach of sacrilegious hands.

   2. Containing sacrilege; as a sacrilegious attempt or act.
